.NET Framework 3.5.name: OVRBoundary
.NET Framework 3.5.summary: Provides access to the Oculus boundary system.

methods.name: GetConfigured()
methods.summary: Returns true if the boundary system is currently configured with valid boundary data.

methods.name: GetDimensions(BoundaryType boundaryType)
methods.summary: Returns a vector that indicates the spatial dimensions of the specified boundary type. (x = width, y = height, z = depth)

methods.name: GetGeometry(BoundaryType boundaryType)
methods.summary: Returns an array of 3d points (in clockwise order) that define the specified boundary type. All points are returned in local tracking space shared by tracked nodes and accessible through OVRCameraRig's trackingSpace anchor.

methods.name: GetVisible()
methods.summary: Returns true if the boundary system is currently visible.

methods.name: ResetLookAndFeel()
methods.summary: Resets the visual look and feel of the boundary system to the initial system settings.

methods.name: SetLookAndFeel(BoundaryLookAndFeel lookAndFeel)
methods.summary: Requests that the visual look and feel of the boundary system be changed as specified. Can be overridden by the system or user.

methods.name: SetVisible(bool value)
methods.summary: Requests that the boundary system visibility be set to the specified value. The actual visibility can be overridden by the system (i.e., proximity trigger) or by the user (boundary system disabled)

methods.name: TestNode(Node node, BoundaryType boundaryType)
methods.summary: Returns the results of testing a tracked node against the specified boundary type. All points are returned in local tracking space shared by tracked nodes and accessible through OVRCameraRig's trackingSpace anchor.
methods.syntax: public BoundaryTestResult TestNode(Node node, BoundaryType boundaryType)
methods.linkedSyntax: public BoundaryTestResult TestNode(Node node, BoundaryType boundaryType)

methods.name: TestPoint(Vector3 point, BoundaryType boundaryType)
methods.summary: Returns the results of testing a 3d point against the specified boundary type. The test point is expected in local tracking space. All points are returned in local tracking space shared by tracked nodes and accessible through OVRCameraRig's trackingSpace anchor.
methods.syntax: public BoundaryTestResult TestPoint(Vector3 point, BoundaryType boundaryType)
methods.linkedSyntax: public BoundaryTestResult TestPoint(Vector3 point, BoundaryType boundaryType)
